Learning Objectives:
~ Use the Windows command line confidently
~ Navigate folders without clicking
~ Find files when you only know their name
~ Read files using the terminal
~ Collect basic system and network information

Notes:
Commands:
- dir: will list down the files and the folders present in the current directory.
- dir /a: shows everything, including hidden items.
- dir /s <file name>: tells Windows to search all subfolders starting from your current directory and show you the full path if the file exists.

** Completed lab on how to use the Windows Command Prompt to navigate files, search for information, and gather basic system details.

Conclusion - learned how to interact with a Windows system using the command line instead of relying on the graphical interface.
